
Problem 1: Kids With the Greatest Number of Candies

Pattern: Array Traversal

Difficulty: Easy

Time Complexity: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(n)

Key Idea:
Find the maximum number of candies among all children using max_element().
Create a boolean vector result initialized with false.
Traverse the array once.

For each child, check if:

candies[i] + extraCandies >= maximum candies
If true, mark result[i] = true.
Return the boolean vector.
What I Learned
How to use max_element() from STL.
Creating and returning a vector<bool>.
Solving array problems by preprocessing (finding the maximum first) before iterating.
